  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently Truffle only supports CommonJS modules for user code like migrations, tests, and exec scripts. EJS modules however are quickly becoming the way of the world. Several very popular node modules have converted over to EJS from CommonJS and won't be supporting CommonJS moving forward.\n\nThere are likely numerous things that need to be done to support this, and I think the NodeJS docs on the [differences between ES modules and CommonJS](https://nodejs.org/api/esm.html#differences-between-es-modules-and-commonjs) are a good starting place to identify what needs to be done.",
